<def f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/corelib/tools/qline.cpp' l='585' ll='595' type='void QLineF::setAngle(qreal angle)'/>
<doc f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/corelib/tools/qline.cpp' l='573'>/*!
    \since 4.4

    Sets the angle of the line to the given \a angle (in degrees).
    This will change the position of the second point of the line such that
    the line has the given angle.

    Positive values for the angles mean counter-clockwise while negative values
    mean the clockwise direction. Zero degrees is at the 3 o&apos;clock position.

    \sa angle()
*/</doc>
